I would agree.  What the hell does that have to do with anything?<br>
<br>
Do you know what you are doing is called?  It is called argumentum ad hominem.  It is a fallacy, and it makes an argument invalid.  That is latin for &quot;attacking the man&quot; instead of the argument.  It occurs when a person attacks their opponent's character or circumstances in an effort to discredit what they say.  An example would be &quot;Well Bishop George's opinion about abortion is wrong because he's a bishop and just a lackey of the Pope!&quot;  You make an attack against the person, and then try to use it as evidence to discredit what they've said.<br>
<br>
Whether or not I have purchased 1000 CDs or 0 CDs has no bearing at all on the truth or falsity of the situation or my stance on it.<br>
<br>
<br>
You know a shaman once said, &quot;shut the fuck up wolvar&quot;, I think you should take that advice.  Why don't you try actually making a valid argument if you're going to tell me my position is wrong instead of your typical &quot;because I say so&quot; shit spewing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuwene>Tuwene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beware the paladin<br>with a map & a plan</span><br>  Posts: 991<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/03 9:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=865.topic&index=116>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: STFUW</span><hr size=1> It's interesting to note how the ISP's are so valiantly defending they're customer's rights to privacy and all that.  I wonder how many people pay $50/mo for broadband instead of $20/mo for dialup in no small part due to wanting to pirate music?  How much money are the ISPs making (indirectly) off of filesharing?<br>
