<br>
Makino - I agree, I can't fathom why in today's day and age, movies come out in Asia and Oceana sometimes 5-8 months after they come out in the US.  Lining up distributors, etc can't be that hard when it's a $330 million dollar movie.  Not to mention that it'd be rather easy to transport it digitally anywhere in the world and the print it to film locally at marginal cost compared to doing all the prints in the US and sending them out to the rest of the world (i have no idea if that's how it's done today, of course - it could already be that a single print just gets mass-copied locally).<br>
